	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span><br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [2.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Um, don't druids get SoW so they can run away if need be?&nbsp;&nbsp;I mean how mobile is a cleric compared to a druid?  Druids are supposed to be more mobile than clerics, so how could you justify giving a "mobile" class plate armor?  This is similar to the rant that rangers should get plate armor.  They are more mobile than say an SK.  To compensate for the lack of plate armor, they get all sorts of abilities that none of the other melee hybrids do.  Plus think for a second, aren't druids supposed to be close to nature?  It wouldn't seem all that natural for a druid to have metal armor.<br><br>Ndarain Darkheart</p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
